    "On the citation network, Figure 5 illustrates the variations in the loss curves for the GCN, GAT, and TWC-GNN techniques.",
    "Compared to the other two models, our proposed TWC-GNN technique achieves a lower final loss value.",
    "The substantially higher loss value in the GCN model can be attributed to its less effective use of higher-order node information and simpler handling of local neighborhood information.",
    "The left half of Figure 6 displays the ground truth labels of the dataset, while the middle part shows the predicted labels.",
    "To facilitate the comparison of anticipated results with ground-truth labels, the right side of the picture uses darker hues to signify correct predictions and lighter shades to highlight prediction mistakes."
